# Splitting
# What Is Traffic Splitting?
#  Traffic splitting lets you send a percentage of incoming requests to different service versions. Common uses include:
#  Canary releases (e.g. send 5% of traffic to v2)
#  A/B testing new features
#  Dark launches (expose hidden features to a subset)
#  Gradual roll-outs to reduce risk

# How Cilium Implements It
   # Gateway API: Kubernetes-native spec for L4–L7 routing.
   # In your HTTPRoute, you list multiple forwardTo targets and assign each an integer weight.
   # The sum of weights defines the 100% split—for example, weights 90 and 10 mean a 90/10 split.
  # Cilium’s eBPF-powered datapath does the actual per-request balancing, with zero side-car overhead.


